1 Division, utility companies, courts, the Department of Corrections, and the Department of Public Health and
2 Human Services, may be used to help maintain the accuracy of voter lists;
3 (5) evaluate how national databases, such as those maintained by the United States Postal
4 Service, could be better utilized to help maintain the accuracy of voter lists;
5 (6) research what other federal data is available regarding citizenship and voting history that may
6 be useful for maintaining the accuracy of voter lists;
7 (7) identify places in which state law needs to be reconciled with federal law; and
8 (8) develop legislation to address these issues and be introduced in the 70th legislative session.
9 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the study include input from appropriate stakeholders, including but
10 not limited to election administrators, the Office of the Secretary of State, and concerned citizens.
11 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that all aspects of the study, including presentation and review
12 requirements, be concluded prior to September 15, 2026.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the final results of the study, including any findings, conclusions,
14 comments, or recommendations of the appropriate committee, be reported to the 70th Legislature.
